4, 2019 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = \n| medaltemplates = \n}}\n\n'''Adam Ozeri''' (born March 7, 1998) is an American professional [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] for [[USL League One]] side [[Orlando City B]] on loan from [[Ferro Carril Oeste]].<ref name=\"SW1\">{{cite news|title=USA - A. Ozeri|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/adam-ozeri/603669/|accessdate=September 14, 2019|work=Soccerway}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nOzeri started his youth career in his homeland with Manhattan Kickers, before switching to TSF Academy soon after.<ref name=\"OWTY1\">{{cite news|title=New Jersey Teen Racing in Argentina|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170204062236/http://owhentheyanks.com/2015/05/08/new-jersey-teen-racing-in-argentina/|accessdate=September 14, 2019|work=O When The Yanks|date=May 8, 2015}}</ref> Ozeri would eventually head to Spain with [[UE Cornell\u00e0|Cornell\u00e0]], notably finishing as top goalscorer in 2014 for the U15s of the [[Catalonia]]-based club.<ref name=\"WOSPAC1\"/> After leaving Cornell\u00e0, Ozeri headed to Argentina with [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]].<ref name=\"WOSPAC1\"/> After time in their youth, he moved over to [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Banfield|Banfield]]'s system.<ref name=\"WOSPAC1\"/><ref name=\"PER1\">{{cite news|title=Alianza Lima: \u00bfQui\u00e9n es Adam Ozeri y de qu\u00e9 juega?|url=https://peru.com/futbol/descentralizado/alianza-lima-quien-adam-ozeri-y-que-juega-noticia-474725|accessdate=September 14, 2019|work=Per\u00fa|date=September 15, 2016}}</ref> In mid-2016, Ozeri was signed by Peru's Alianza Lima; though would see no senior action.<ref name=\"OVA1\">{{cite news|title=Ozeri: \"Es un gran desaf\u00edo para m\u00ed ir a Alianza Lima\"|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161109065056/http://ovacion.pe:80/alianza-lima/ozeri-gran-desafio-para-mi-ir-alianza-lima|accessdate=September 14, 2019|work=Ovaci\u00f3n|date=September 3, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"DEP1\">{{cite news|title=Alianza Lima: Adam Ozeri, la promesa estadounidense que fich\u00f3 por los \u00edntimos|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114100339/http://depor.com:80/futbol-peruano/adam-ozeri-promesa-estadounidense-que-alianza-lima-ficho-1079304|accessdate=September 14, 2019|work=Depor|date=September 3, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"EB1\">{{cite news|title=Alianza Lima: el fichaje 'fantasma' que no conoces|url=https://elbocon.pe/futbol-peruano/alianza-lima-quien-es-y-como-juega-el-jale-adam-ozeri-130749/|accessdate=September 14, 2019|work=El Boc\u00f3n|date=January 15, 2017}}</ref> In 2017, Ozeri sealed a return to Argentina with [[Ferro Carril Oeste]].<ref name=\"SA1\">{{cite news|title=Qui\u00e9n es Adam Ozeri|url=http://soloascenso.com.ar/notas/ferro-carril-oeste/quien-es-adam-ozeri/138514|accessdate=September 14, 2019|work=Solo Ascenso|date=September 12, 2019}}</ref> February 2019 saw Ozeri depart on loan to Brazilian [[Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie D|S\u00e9rie D]] outfit [[Boavista Sport Club|Boavista]].<ref name=\"MA1\">{{cite news|title=Se va para Brasil|url=https://www.mundoascenso.com.ar/noticia/97116-se-va-para-brasil|accessdate=September 14, 2019|work=Mundo Ascenso|date=January 18, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"BOA1\">{{cite news|title=Volante americano que estava na Argentina treina no Boavista e pode ser refor\u00e7o|url=https://www.boavistasportclub.com.br/noticias/volante-americano-que-estava-na-argentina-treina-no-boavista-e-pode-ser-reforco/|accessdate=September 14, 2019|work=Boavista|date=February 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter featuring four times, including twice against [[Sport Club Ga\u00facho|Ga\u00facho]], for Boavista, Ozeri went back to Ferro Carril Oeste ahead of the 2019\u201320 campaign in [[Primera B Nacional]].<ref name=\"SW1\"/> His first appearance subsequently arrived, as he played the full duration of a 2\u20131 defeat away to [[Estudiantes de R\u00edo Cuarto|Estudiantes]] on September 13.<ref name=\"SW1\"/><ref name=\"ATD1\">{{cite news|title=De la \"Gran manzana\" a Caballito|url=https://altoquedeportes.com.ar/noticias/ver/40772|accessdate=September 21, 2019|work=Al Toque Deportes|date=September 17, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n2014 saw Ozeri participate in training camps with both Israel and the United States at youth level.<ref name=\"OWTY1\"/> In August 2016, Ozeri was called up to the latter's U19s by [[Brad Friedel]] for the subsequent month's Stevan Vilotic Tournament in [[Subotica]], Serbia.<ref name=\"US1\">{{cite news|title=Friedel Names 20-Player Roster for 2016 Stevan Vilotic Tournament|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170707083957/http://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2016/08/30/20/13/160830-u19mnt-friedel-names-20-player-roster-for-2016-stevan-vilotic-tournament|accessdate=September 14, 2019|work=United States Soccer Federation|date=August 30, 2016}}</ref> He also made Friedel's squad for a training camp in the succeeding November.<ref name=\"US2\">{{cite news|title=Friedel Calls 19 Players for Final U-19 MNT Training Camp of 2016|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606090524/http://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2016/11/04/22/00/161104-u19mnt-friedel-calls-19-players-for-final-training-camp-of-2016|accessdate=September 14, 2019|work=United States Soccer Federation|date=November 4, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|September 14, 2019}}.<ref name=\"SW1\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Ferro Carril Oeste]]\n|[[2018\u201319 Primera B Nacional|2018\u201319]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Primera B Nacional]]\n|0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0||0||0||0\n|-