{"title_page": "Blanche Stocker", "text_new": "{{inuse}}\n[[File:Blanche Stocker 1906.jpg|thumb|right|Blanche Stocker in 1906]]\n'''Blanche Eleanor Stocker''' (20 July 1884 &ndash; 1950) was a British [[stage beauty]], [[Edwardian musical comedy]] stage and [[silent film]] actress and singer.\n\nStocker was born in [[Mumbai|Bombay]] in India in 1884. She was Lucille in ''[[The Belle of Brittany]]'' at the [[Queen's Theatre]] (1908); Lady Sybil Julia James on ''[[Our Miss Gibbs]]'' at the [[Gaiety Theatre, London|Gaiety Theatre]] (1909);<ref>[\nhttps://theatricalia.com/play/2ae/our-miss-gibbs/production/5ex Cast of ''Our Miss Gibbs'' - Theatricalia website]</ref> Viola in ''[[Filmzauber#The_Girl_on_the_Film|The Girl on the Film]]'' at the [[Gaiety Theatre, London|Gaiety Theatre]] in the [[West End of London]] (1913) and later the same year at the [[44th Street Theatre]] on [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]];<ref>[https://www.broadwayworld.com/shows/The-Girl-on-the-Film-1534.html ''The Girl on the Film'' on Broadway - broadwayworld.com]</ref> Ruth Goldman/Miss Cohen in ''[[Potash and Perlmutter]]'' at the [[Queen's Theatre]] (1914-15); and Lady-in-Waiting in ''[[Arlette (musical)|Arlette]]'' at the [[Shaftesbury Theatre]] (1917).<ref>[[J. P. Wearing]], [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=KMFnAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT610&lpg ''The London Stage 1910-1919: A Calendar of Productions, Performers, and Personnel''], Rowman & Littlefield (2014) - Google Books</ref> A [[silent film]] actress, she played Jane in ''Winning a Widow'' (1910).<ref>[https://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/540f7b8ea4d4e Blanche Stocker - [[British Film Institute]] Database]</ref>\n\nHer younger sister Doris Stocker was also a singer and actress.\n\nBlanche Stocker died in [[Kensington]] in London in 1950 aged 65. She never married.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.npg.org.uk/collections/search/person/mp65483/blanche-stocker Photographic portraits of Blanche Stocker - [[National Portrait Gallery, London]]]\n*[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3100338/ Blanche Stocker on [[Internet Movie Database]]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stocker, Blanche}}\n[[Category:1884 births]]\n[[Category:1950 deaths]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Mumbai]]\n", "text_old": "{{inuse}}\n[[File:Blanche Stocker 1906.jpg|thumb|right|Blanche Stocker in 1906]]\n'''Blanche Eleanor Stocker''' (20 July 1884 &ndash; 1950) was a British [[stage beauty]], [[Edwardian musical comedy]] stage and [[silent film]] actress and singer.\n\nStocker was born in [[Mumbai|Bombay]] in India in 1884. She was Lucille in ''[[The Belle of Brittany]]'' at the [[Queen's Theatre]] (1908); Lady Sybil Julia James on ''[[Our Miss Gibbs]]'' at the [[Gaiety Theatre, London|Gaiety Theatre]] (1909);<ref>[\nhttps://theatricalia.com/play/2ae/our-miss-gibbs/production/5ex Cast of ''Our Miss Gibbs'' - Theatricalia website]</ref> Viola in ''[[Filmzauber#The_Girl_on_the_Film|The Girl on the Film]]'' at the [[Gaiety Theatre, London|Gaiety Theatre]] in the [[West End of London]] (1913) and later the same year at the [[44th Street Theatre]] on [[Broadway Theatre|Broadway];<ref>[https://www.broadwayworld.com/shows/The-Girl-on-the-Film-1534.html ''The Girl on the Film'' on Broadway - broadwayworld.com]</ref> Ruth Goldman/Miss Cohen in ''[[Potash and Perlmutter]]'' at the [[Queen's Theatre]] (1914-15); and Lady-in-Waiting in ''[[Arlette (musical)|Arlette]]'' at the [[Shaftesbury Theatre]] (1917).<ref>[[J. P. Wearing]], [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=KMFnAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT610&lpg ''The London Stage 1910-1919: A Calendar of Productions, Performers, and Personnel''], Rowman & Littlefield (2014) - Google Books</ref> A [[silent film]] actress, she played Jane in ''Winning a Widow'' (1910).<ref>[https://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/540f7b8ea4d4e Blanche Stocker - [[British Film Institute]] Database]</ref>\n\nHer younger sister Doris Stocker was also a singer and actress.\n\nBlanche Stocker died in [[Kensington]] in London in 1950 aged 65. She never married.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.npg.org.uk/collections/search/person/mp65483/blanche-stocker Photographic portraits of Blanche Stocker - [[National Portrait Gallery, London]]]\n*[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3100338/ Blanche Stocker on [[Internet Movie Database]]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stocker, Blanche}}\n[[Category:1884 births]]\n[[Category:1950 deaths]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Mumbai]]\n", "name_user": "Station1", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blanche_Stocker"}
